RIYADH: Saudi Arabia announced two deaths from COVID-19 and 43 new infections on Saturday. Of the new cases, 13 were recorded in Riyadh, eight in Jeddah, two in Buraidah, two in Madinah, two in Makkah, and two in Dhahran. Several other cities recorded one new case each. The total number of recoveries in the Kingdom increased to 537,246 after 38 more patients recovered from the virus. A total of 8,776 people have succumbed to the virus in the Kingdom so far. Over 45 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine have been administered in the Kingdom to date.